Let me fill you in!!

Okay, so on Sunday, I had the bright idea to dye my hair black. My mom planned on doing it, but she decided not to, so we had extra dye. So I do it, and I get dye all over my face, of course. So I try to get it off, and most of it does come off, excpet for this giant thing on the side of my face. I started trying to rub it off, and i just ended up rubbing a good protion of my FACE OFF. So, now I have a black blotch on my face, and a burn in the center of it. Nice, I know. So then, Monday I have a game that  I find out about an hour before the bus leaves. (Thanks, by the way, Brianna). I go, and I don't play for about the first half. Then, about 3/4 of the way through the second half, the coach puts me and I'm in for the rest of the game. When the game's almost done, me and this girl both go for the ball, and we collide and smash heads. I walk away with a bump above my head, and she gets driven away in an ambulance. She had a concussion! I felt so bad, I wanted to apologize, so I did to the coach and he said he'd pass it on. The bump's pretty big, it doesn't really hurt, but oh well. So now I have a bump, a burn, and a blotch. Fun fun fun. So yep, the varsity won too, that was an awesome game. They destroyed the other team, ours was like an underdog story. We were losing in the first half, and then they put me (hah, not to sound conceited).



Love
Jill
